NAME
	msync - very naiv tool for one way synchronization

SYNOPSIS
	msync [options] <source> <target>
	msync [options] -i 'ssh synergy4' -o adfadf

	paths are aliases for
	msync -s -p /tmp/
	msync slave chroot?

DESCRIPTION

	directories in the form:
		ssh:///user@host/directory
		ssh://host/directory
		file:///directory
		/directory
		directory

	options:
		-v	--version 
		-h	--help
		-t	--time TIME
		-d	--dry-run
		-a	--adjust / --slacktime  seconds: extract <seconds> from the newest source-file-timestamp

	TIME
		yesterday		- copy files since yesterdays at 00:00:00
		midnight		- copy files newer than midnight
		+"2007-01-01"	- iso 8601 (Y-m-d)
		+"03823232"
		.. anything else will be interpret as a filepath/directory, which will be scanned to determine the newest timestamp

* Check if multiple machines is used (ssh:), if so, determine time-offsets otherwise use 0 as offsets

http://miek.nl/projects/rdup/doc.html
